''' Won both tournaments in the same year\n|[[Rod Laver]] <br>[[Bj\u00f6rn Borg]] <br>[[Roger Federer]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" |French Open \n|2008, 2010, 2017\n|[[Open Era tennis records \u2013 men's singles#Career achievements|3 grand slam wins without losing a set]]<ref name=\"RGrecords\" />\n|Bj\u00f6rn Borg\n|-\n|2005-2019\n|12 finals at the same tournament\n|Roger Federer\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" |French Open - French Open \n|2005-2019\n|Won a grand slam in teens, twenties, and thirties<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.in/tennis/story/_/id/19605999/by-numbers-rafael-nadal-record-breaking-10th-french-open-title |title=Nadal's quest to reach La D\u00e9cima |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=18 June 2017}}</ref>\n|Ken Rosewall <br>[[Pete Sampras]]\n|-\n|2005-2014, 2017, 2018, 2019\n|Won at least one grand slam title in 13 years\n|'''Stands alone'''\n|-\n|}\n* Nadal is one of only two players in the Open Era to make 5+ finals on clay (12), grass (5), and hard courts (9).  The only other player is [[Roger Federer]]; clay (5), grass (11), hard (14).\n* Nadal is one of only two players in the Open Era to make 5+ finals at each of the grand slams, 5 Australian Open, 12 French Open, 5 Wimbledon, and 5 US Open. The other is Federer (7, 5, 11, 7).\n* Rafa is one of only five men to have won the US Open 4+ times.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.atptour.com/en/news/us-open-2019-final-nadal-medvedev |title=Nadal Sprints To Third US Open Crown |publisher=ATP World Tour |accessdate=8 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Records at each Grand Slam Tournament ==\n* These records were attained in the [[Open Era]] of tennis, since 1968.\n* Records in ''italics'' are currently active streaks.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Tournament \n!Year(s)\n!Record accomplished\n!Players tied\n|-\n|'''[[Australian Open]]'''\n|2012||[[2012 Australian Open \u2013 Men's Singles final|Longest Grand Slam final (by duration)]] vs. Novak Djokovic{{#tag:ref|The final took 5 hours, 53 minutes to complete.<ref name=\"AOfinal\">{