urface win streak]] (Clay courts - 81)\n|'''Stands alone'''\n|-\n|13 consecutive clay court titles\n|'''Stands alone'''\n|-\n|2005-2008\n|18 consecutive clay court finals\n|'''Stands alone'''\n|-\n|2013\n|Won 35+ matches on clay courts and 35+ matches on hard courts in single calendar season\n|'''Stands alone'''\n|-\n|2017-2018\n|[[Rafael Nadal career statistics#46 consecutive clay sets streak|Won 50 consecutive sets at a single surface (clay)]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/tennis/44077250 |title=Madrid Open: Rafael Nadal breaks John McEnroe's 34-year-old set record |publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=11 May 2018}}</ref>\n|'''Stands alone'''\n|-\n|2004-2019\n|[[List of career achievements by Rafael Nadal#Wins over No. 1 players|20 match wins against world No. 1 players]]<sup>[h]</sup>\n|'''Stands alone'''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2004-2006\n|16 titles won as a teenager (18-y/o - 6 titles & 19-y/o - 10 titles)\n|[[Bj\u00f6rn Borg]]\n|-\n|Won 17 of his first 19 finals appearances (17-2)\n|'''Stands alone'''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2005\n|11 titles won in a single season as a teenager\n|'''Stands alone'''\n|-\n|Won 24 consecutive matches as a teenager\n|'''Stands alone'''\n|-\n|2004-2020\n|[[Open Era tennis records \u2013 men's singles#Per year cumulative records|17 consecutive years winning 1+ title]]\n|'''Stands alone'''\n|-\n|2005, 2007, 2015\n|3 [[Stuttgart Open]] titles\n|'''Stands alone'''\n|-\n|}\n* The only player to have lost just one game in an ATP World Tour Masters 1000 final ([[2010 Monte-Carlo Rolex Masters \u2013 Singles#Finals|Monte Carlo 2010: 6\u20130, 6\u20131]]).\n* The fastest to win ATP Masters Titles (since winning the first title):<br> 5 titles: 8 tournaments/1 year: [[2005 Monte Carlo Masters \u2013 Singles|Monte Carlo 2005]] \u2013 [[2006 Monte Carlo Masters \u2013 Singles|Monte Carlo 2006]]<br>10 titles: 24 tournaments/3 years: [[2005 Monte Carlo Masters \u2013 Singles|Monte Carlo 2005]] \u2013 [[2008 Monte Carlo Masters \u2013 Singles|Monte Carlo 2008]]<br>15 titles: 34 tournaments/4 years: [[2005 Monte Carlo Masters \u2013 Singles|Monte Carlo 2005]] \u2013 [[2009 Internazionali BNL d'Italia|Rome 2009]]<br>20 titles: 58 tournaments/7 years: [[2005 Monte Carlo Masters \u2013 Singles|Monte Carlo 2005]] \u2013 [[2012 Monte-Carlo Rolex Masters \u2013 Singles|Monte Carlo 2012]]<br>25 titles: 65 tournaments/8 years: [[2005 Monte Carlo Masters \u2013 Singles|Monte Carlo 2005]] \u2013 [[2013 Rogers Cup \u2013 Men's Singles|Montreal 2013]]<br>35 titles: 108 tournaments/14 years: [[2005 Monte Carlo Masters \u2013 Singles|Monte Carlo 2005]] \u2013 [[2019 Rogers Cup \u2013 Men's Singles|Montreal 2019]]\n\n==Guinness World Records==\nAs of 2019, Nadal holds 21 Guinness World Records.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://guinnessworldrecords.com/search/applicationrecordsearch?term=Rafael+Nadal&contentType=record|title=Guinness Records online registry, requires signing in.|website=Guinness World Records|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-07-16}}</ref>\n# Most consecutive French Open singles tennis titles won by a man - 5\n# Most consecutive Grand Slam singles final losses by a man - 3\n# Youngest man to win a tennis career Grand Slam at {{Age in years, months and days|1986|6|3|2010|9|13}}\n# Most Men\u2019s ATP titles won outdoors\n# Most consecutive years winning an ATP title\n# Most titles of one Grand Slam singles tennis tournament - 12\n# Most French Open singles tennis titles won by a man - 12\n# First player to win 10 singles titles at the same ATP World Tour event (Open Era)\n# Most consecutive sets won on a single surface - 50 on clay\n# Most ATP Masters 1000 singles titles won in a career - 35\n# First player to win 10 singles titles at the same Grand Slam (Open Era) - Roland Garros 12\n# Most tennis singles matches on clay won consecutively (male) - 81 clay\n# Most wins of one Grand Slam singles tennis tournament (Open Era, male)\n# Most wins of one Grand Slam singles tennis tournament (Open Era)\n# Most clay-court singles titles (Open Era) - 59\n# Longest Grand Slam tennis final - 2012 Australian Open\n# Most ATP Tour singles matches between two players (Open Era)\n# Longest tennis Wimbledon singles final (male)\n# Most singles finals played at one Grand Slam tennis tournament (Open Era)\n# First players to win all four tennis Grand Slams together\n# Most wins of one singles tennis tournament, [[Monte Carlo|Monte-Carlo Masters]] (Open Era)\n\n== Wins over No. 1 players ==\n\nNadal holds the solo record for most wins against No. 1-ranked players, 20. With his win over Djokovic, he broke a long-standing tie with [[Boris Becker]].  He recorded 13 wins over [[Roger Federer]] and 7 wins over [[Novak Djokovic]].  Nadal recorded his first win over a No. 1-ranked player when he was only {{Age in years, months and days|1986|6|3|2004|3|28}}, and ranked No. 34, when he beat Federer in straight sets in the third round of the [[2004 NASDAQ-100 Open \u2013 Men's Singles#Top Half|2004 Miami Open]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/tennis/5/en/players/playerprofiles/rankhistory.asp?playernumber=N409&selyear=2004|title=Rafael Nadal's 2004 Ranking History|publisher=ATP's official site|accessdate=14 February 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090325052656/http://www.atpworldtour.com/tennis/5/en/players/playerprofiles/rankhistory.asp?playernumber=N409&selyear=2004|archivedate=25 March 2009}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n!#\n!width=200|Player\n!width=275|Event\n!Surface\n!Rd\n!width=220|Score\n|-\n|1.\n|{{flagicon|SUI}} [[Roger Federer]]\n| bgcolor=\"#e9e9e9\" |[[2004 NASDAQ-100 Open \u2013 Men's Singles#Top Half|2004 Miami]], United States\n|style=\"background:#ccf;\"|Hard\n| bgcolor=\"#afeeee\" |3R\n|6\u20133, 6\u20133\n|-\n|2.\n|{{flagicon|SUI}} Roger Federer\n| bgcolor=\"#f3e6d7\" |[[2005 French Open \u2013 Men's Singles#Finals|2005 French Open]], Paris, France\n|style=\"background:#ebc2af;\"|Clay\n|bgcolor=yellow|SF\n|6\u20133, 4\u201