 on the Run (1936 film)|Love on the Run]]'' || Sally Parker || [[W. S. Van Dyke]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1937 || ''[[The Last of Mrs. Cheyney (1937 film)|The Last of Mrs. Cheyney]]'' || Fay Cheyney || [[Richard Boleslawski]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1937 || ''[[The Bride Wore Red]]'' || Anni Pavlovitch || [[Dorothy Arzner]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1937 || ''[[Mannequin (1937 film)|Mannequin]]'' || Jessica Cassidy || [[Frank Borzage]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1938 || ''[[The Shining Hour]]'' || Olivia Riley || [[Frank Borzage]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1939 || ''[[The Ice Follies of 1939]]'' || Mary McKay || [[Reinhold Sch\u00fcnzel]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1939 || ''[[The Women (1939 film)|The Women]]'' || Crystal Allen || [[George Cukor]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1940 || ''[[Strange Cargo (1940 film)|Strange Cargo]]'' || Julie || [[Frank Borzage]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1940 || ''[[Susan and God]]'' || Susan Trexel || [[George Cukor]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1941 || ''[[A Woman's Face]]'' || Anna Holm || [[George Cukor]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1941 || ''[[When Ladies Meet (1941 film)|When Ladies Meet]]'' || Mary Howard || [[Robert Z. Leonard]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1942 || ''[[They All Kissed the Bride]]'' || Margaret Drew || [[Alexander Hall]] || [[Columbia Pictures|Columbia]]\n|-\n| 1942 || ''[[Reunion in France]]'' || Michele de la Becque || [[Jules Dassin]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1943 || ''[[Above Suspicion (1943 film)|Above Suspicion]]'' || Frances Myles || [[Richard Thorpe]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1944 || ''[[Hollywood Canteen (film)|Hollywood Canteen]]'' || Herself (cameo role) || [[Delmer Daves]] || [[Warner Bros.]]\n|-\n| 1945 || ''[[Mildred Pierce (film)|Mildred Pierce]]'' || Mildred Pierce || [[Michael Curtiz]] || [[Warner Bros.]]\n|-\n| 1946 || ''[[Humoresque (1946 film)|Humoresque]]'' || Helen Wright || [[Jean Negulesco]