{"title_page": "Minor Raja", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Minor Raja\n| image          =\n| caption        =\n| writer         = [[Jandhyala Subramanya Sastry|Jandhyala]] {{small|(dialogues)}}\n| story          = [[P. Kalaimani]]\n| screenplay     = \n| producer       = Venigalla Rambabu <br /> K. P. Panakala Rao\n| director       = Katragadda Ravi Teja\n| starring       = [[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]]<br />[[Shobana]]<br />Rekha \n| music          = [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]\n| cinematography = K. Ram Gopal Reddy\n| editing        = V. Suresh Kumar\n| based on       = ''[[Mallu Vetti Minor]]'' (1990)\n| studio         = Rakesh Productions<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1579634/ |title=Minor Raja (Overview) |work=IMDb}}</ref>\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|1991||}}\n| runtime        = 136 mins\n| country        = India\n| language       = Telugu\n| budget         =\n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Minor Raja''''' is a 1991 [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] [[comedy film]], produced by Venigalla Rambabu, K. P. Panakala Rao under the Rakesh Productions banner<ref>{{cite web|url=http://telugumoviepedia.com/movie/cast/699/minor-raja-cast.html |title=Minor Raja (Banner) |work=Chitr.com}}</ref> and directed by Katragadda Ravi Teja.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.knowyourfilms.com/film/Minor-Raja/19165 |title=Minor Raja (Direction) |work=Know Your Films}}</ref> It stars [[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]], [[Shobana]] and Rekha in the lead roles,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gomolo.com/minor-raajaa-movie/18016 |title=Minor Raja (Cast & Crew) |work=gomolo.com}}</ref> with music composed by [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://spicyonion.com/title/minor-raja-telugu-movie/ |title=Minor Raja (Music) |work=Spicy Onion}}</ref> The film is remake of the [[Tamil language|Tamil]] film ''[[Mallu Vetti Minor]]'' (1990). The film was recorded as a ''flop'' at the box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thecinebay.com/movie/index/id/4330?ed=Tolly |title=Minor Raja (Review) |work=The Cine Bay}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nMinor Raja (Rajendra Prasad), was a rich man and wayward village playboy, who spent his time in brothels like his father. Santhana Lakshmi (Shobhana) and Minor Raja fell in love with each other. Minor Raja and President (Kota Srinivasa Rao) were in a feud for several years. In a misunderstanding, When Minor Raja's detractors wrongly accuse a teacher Seeta (Rekha) of having an affair with him, he decides to marry her to save her the humiliation. Minor Raja had to marry her. A few years later, Minor Raja became the perfect husband and had a son. While Santhana Lakshmi was still unmarried, she teased Minor Raja whenever she got the opportunity. One day, it was \"the straw that broke the camel's back\" so the angry Minor Raja raped Santhana Lakshmi. The rest of the story is what happens to Minor Raja, Seeta, and Santhana Lakshmi.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]] as Minor Raja\n*[[Shobana]] as Santhana Lakshmi\n*[[Rekha (South Indian actress)|Rekha]] as Seeta\n*[[Kota Srinivasa Rao]]\n*[[Brahmanandam]]\n*[[Mallikarjuna Rao (actor)|Mallikarjuna Rao]]\n*[[Narra Venkateswara Rao]]\n*[[Gundu Hanumantha Rao]]\n*[[Subbaraya Sharma]]\n*Sanjeevi\n*Anitha\n*Mamatha\n*Chilakala Radha\n*[[Jaya Malini]]\n*[[Y. Vijaya]]\n{{colend}}\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Minor Raja\n| type       = film\n| artist     = [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1990\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = Soundtrack\n| length     = 28:53\n| label      =\n| producer   = [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]\n| prev_title = Sarpayaagam\n| prev_year  = 1991\n| next_title = [[Teneteega (1991 film)|Teneteega]]\n| next_year  = 1991\n}}\n\nMusic composed by [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]. Music released on Music Company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cineradham.com/telugu-audio/movie/3735/Minor%20Raja%20(1991)/ |title=Minor Raja (Songs) |work=Cineradham}}</ref>\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed =\n| headline =\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = 28:53\n| all_writing =\n| all_lyrics =\n| all_music =\n| title1  = Manase Dhochukune\n| lyrics1 = Jaladi\n| extra1  = [[V. Ramakrishna]], [[Jikki]]\n| length1 = 5:00\n\n| title2  = Cheliya \n| lyrics2 = [[Veturi Sundararama Murthy]]\n| extra2  = [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam|SP Balu]], [[K. S. Chithra|Chitra]]\n| length2 = 4:51\n\n| title3  = Nadiveedhilo Amma \n| lyrics3 = Veturi Sundararama Murthy\n| extra3  = [[K. J. Yesudas]], Chitra\n| length3 = 4:30\n\n| title4  = O Madana Sundara \n| lyrics4 = Veturi Sundararama Murthy\n| extra4  = SP Balu, Chitra, [[S. P. Sailaja]]\n| length4 = 4:31\n\n| title5  = Vennella Vedikkinche \n| lyrics5 = Veturi Sundararama Murthy \n| extra5  = SP Balu, Chitra\n| length5 = 4:54\n\n| title6  = Yendammo Magasiri\n| lyrics6 = Veturi Sundararama Murthy \n| extra6  = Chitra\n| length6 = 5:07\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n<!-- After listing your sources please cite them using inline citations and place them after the information they cite. Please see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n*\n*\n*\n*\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:1990s Telugu-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Telugu remakes of Tamil films]]\n[[Category:Telugu films scored by Vidyasagar]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Minor Raja\n| image          =\n| caption        =\n| writer         = [[Jandhyala Subramanya Sastry|Jandhyala]] {{small|(dialogues)}}\n| story          = [[P. Kalaimani]]\n| screenplay     = \n| producer       = Venigalla Rambabu <br /> K. P. Panakala Rao\n| director       = Katragadda Ravi Teja\n| starring       = [[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]]<br />[[Shobana]]<br />Rekha \n| music          = [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]\n| cinematography = K. Ram Gopal Reddy\n| editing        = V. Suresh Kumar\n| based on       = ''[[Mallu Vetti Minor]]'' (1990)\n| studio         = Rakesh Productions<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1579634/ |title=Minor Raja (Overview) |work=IMDb}}</ref>\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|1991||}}\n| runtime        = 136 mins\n| country        = India\n| language       = Telugu\n| budget         =\n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Minor Raja''''' is a 1991 [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] [[comedy film]], produced by Venigalla Rambabu, K. P. Panakala Rao under the Rakesh Productions banner<ref>{{cite web|url=http://telugumoviepedia.com/movie/cast/699/minor-raja-cast.html |title=Minor Raja (Banner) |work=Chitr.com}}</ref> and directed by Katragadda Ravi Teja.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.knowyourfilms.com/film/Minor-Raja/19165 |title=Minor Raja (Direction) |work=Know Your Films}}</ref> It stars [[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]], [[Shobana]] and Rekha in the lead roles,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gomolo.com/minor-raajaa-movie/18016 |title=Minor Raja (Cast & Crew) |work=gomolo.com}}</ref> with music composed by [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://spicyonion.com/title/minor-raja-telugu-movie/ |title=Minor Raja (Music) |work=Spicy Onion}}</ref> The film is remake of the [[Tamil language|Tamil]] film ''[[Mallu Vetti Minor]]'' (1990). The film was recorded as a ''flop'' at the box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thecinebay.com/movie/index/id/4330?ed=Tolly |title=Minor Raja (Review) |work=The Cine Bay}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nMinor Raja (Rajendra Prasad), was a rich man and wayward village playboy, who spent his time in brothels like his father. Santhana Lakshmi (Shobhana) and Minor Raja fell in love with each other. Minor Raja and President (Kota Srinivasa Rao) were in a feud for several years. In a misunderstanding, When Minor Raja's detractors wrongly accuse a teacher Seeta (Rekha) of having an affair with him, he decides to marry her to save her the humiliation. Minor Raja had to get married to her. A few years later, Minor Raja became the perfect husband and had a son. While Santhana Lakshmi was still unmarried, she teased Minor Raja whenever she got the opportunity. One day, it was \"the straw that broke the camel's back\" so the angry Minor Raja raped Santhana Lakshmi. The rest of the story is what happens to Minor Raja, Seeta, and Santhana Lakshmi.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]] as Minor Raja\n*[[Shobana]] as Santhana Lakshmi\n*[[Rekha (South Indian actress)|Rekha]] as Seeta\n*[[Kota Srinivasa Rao]]\n*[[Brahmanandam]]\n*[[Mallikarjuna Rao (actor)|Mallikarjuna Rao]]\n*[[Narra Venkateswara Rao]]\n*[[Gundu Hanumantha Rao]]\n*[[Subbaraya Sharma]]\n*Sanjeevi\n*Anitha\n*Mamatha\n*Chilakala Radha\n*[[Jaya Malini]]\n*[[Y. Vijaya]]\n{{colend}}\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Minor Raja\n| type       = film\n| artist     = [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1990\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = Soundtrack\n| length     = 28:53\n| label      =\n| producer   = [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]\n| prev_title = Sarpayaagam\n| prev_year  = 1991\n| next_title = [[Teneteega (1991 film)|Teneteega]]\n| next_year  = 1991\n}}\n\nMusic composed by [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]. Music released on Music Company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cineradham.com/telugu-audio/movie/3735/Minor%20Raja%20(1991)/ |title=Minor Raja (Songs) |work=Cineradham}}</ref>\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed =\n| headline =\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = 28:53\n| all_writing =\n| all_lyrics =\n| all_music =\n| title1  = Manase Dhochukune\n| lyrics1 = Jaladi\n| extra1  = [[V. Ramakrishna]], [[Jikki]]\