]]|title=That\u2019s Not What We Call Music: 19 Unfathomably Popular Albums Of The 00s |date=September 23, 2014 |accessdate=2017-02-25|quote=Let us be frank: Dido\u2019s debut, \u2018No Angel\u2019, wasn\u2019t much cop either. But it was superior to follow-up \u2018Life For Rent\u2019, which sold over 12 million copies worldwide and was the seventh best-selling album of the 2000\u2019s in the UK.|first=Emily |last=Barker}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |2003\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |''[[Get Rich or Die Tryin' (album)|Get Rich or Die Tryin'<nowiki/>]]''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |[[50 Cent]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{Flagu|United States}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''12.0'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2013/02/check-out-an-infographic-of-50-cents-career-by-the-numbers|title=Check Out an Infographic of 50 Cent's Career By the Numbers|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=February 6, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|2008\n|''[[Sleep Through the Static]]''\n|[[Jack Johnson (musician)|Jack Johnson]]\n|{{Flagu|United States}}\n|'''12.0'''\n|<ref name=\":0\" />\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |2003\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |''[[Dangerously in Love]]''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |[[Beyonc\u00e9]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |{{Flagu|United States}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |'''11.0'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=\"rapfix\">{{cite news |last=Chandler |first=D. L. |url=http://rapfix.mtv.com/2011/04/05/jay-z-and-beyonce-celebrate-three-years-of-wedded-bliss/ |title=Jay-Z And Beyonc\u00e9 Celebrate Three Years Of Wedded Bliss |publisher=MTV Rapfix. Viacom |date=April 5, 2011 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/654RvFtZI?url=http://rapfix.mtv.com/2011/04/05/jay-z-and-beyonce-celebrate-three-years-of-wedded-bliss/ |archivedate=January 30, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |2004\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |''[[Ba